==Hindi==
===Demonstrative pronoun===
'''उस''' (us)

# [[that]] - [[oblique]] case only, see below for direct. (Plural: [[उन]])
#:Example: "उस मकान [[में]] [[छह]] कमरे हैं" - "In that house there are six rooms." Literally - "These houses in six rooms are."
# [[him]] - oblique case only, far reference. (If [[respect]] is conveyed, [[उन]] is used)
#:Example: "उसको [[पैसे]] [[देना|दे]] [[दो]]" - Give money to him. Literally "Him to money give."
# [[her]] - oblique case only, far reference. (If [[respect]] is conveyed, उन is used)
#:Example "उसको पैसे दे दो" - Give money to her. (The same)
# [[it]] - oblique case only.
#:Example "उस [[लेना|लो]]" - Take those.

====Inflection====
[[Direct]]: [[वह]](vah)
Direct, plural, far reference: [[वे]](ve)

===See also===
*[[इस]](is) - [[This]], [[him]] and [[her]] (near reference).

